[section#exec.recv.concepts
    [:en] Receiver concepts
    [:zh_CN] 接收器概念
]

[para]
[:en] A receiver represents the continuation of an asynchronous operation.
[:zh_CN] 接收器表示异步操作的继续。

[:en] The [`:c receiver] concept defines the requirements for a receiver type ([#exec.async.ops]).
[:zh_CN] [`:c receiver] 概念定义针对接收器类型的要求（[#exec.async.ops]）。

[:en] The exposition-only concept [`:c receiver-of] defines the requirements for
a receiver type that is usable as the first argument of a set of completion operations
corresponding to a set of completion signatures.
[:zh_CN] 仅用于阐释的概念 [`:c receiver-of] 定义对可用作对应于某完成签名集合的
完成操作集合的第一个实参的接收器类型的要求。

[:en] The [`get_env] customization point object is used to access
a receiver[=']s associated environment.
[:zh_CN] [`get_env] 定制化点对象用于访问接收器的关联环境。

[codeblock:synopsis]
namespace std::execution {
  template<class Rcvr>
    concept [[redoc("`:c@def>")]]receiver =
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]derived_from<typename remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>::receiver_concept, receiver_tag> &&
      requires(const remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>& rcvr) {
        { get_env(rcvr) } -> [[redoc("*:c>")]]queryable;
      } &&
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]move_constructible<remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>> &&               // [:en] rvalues are movable, and [:zh_CN] 右值是可移动的，
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]constructible_from<remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>, Rcvr> &&         // [:en@~] lvalues are copyable, and [:zh_CN@~] 左值是可复制的，且
      is_nothrow_move_constructible_v<remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>>;    // [:en@~] no-throw-movable [:zh_CN@~] 可无抛出移动的

  template<class Signature, class Rcvr>
    concept [[redoc("*:c@def>")]]valid-completion-for =                              // [=expos]
      requires (Signature* sig) {
        []<class Tag, class... Args>(Tag(*)(Args...))
            requires [[redoc("*:c>"")]]callable<Tag, remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>, Args...>
        {}(sig);
      };

  template<class Rcvr, class Completions>
    concept [[redoc("*:c@def>")]]has-completions =                                   // [=expos]
      requires (Completions* completions) {
        []<[[redoc("*:c>"")]]valid-completion-for<Rcvr>...Sigs>(completion_signatures<Sigs...>*)
        {}(completions);
      };

  template<class Rcvr, class Completions>
    concept [[redoc("*:c@def>")]]receiver-of =                                       // [=expos]
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]receiver<Rcvr> && [[redoc("*:c>")]]has-completions<Rcvr, Completions>;
}
[codeblock:end]

[para]
[:en] Class types that are marked [`final] do not model the [`:c receiver] concept.
[:zh_CN] 标有 [`final] 的类类型不构成 [`:c receiver] 概念。

[para]
[:en] Let [`rcvr] be a receiver and let [`op_state] be an operation state associated
with an asynchronous operation created by connecting [`rcvr] with a sender.
[:zh_CN] 令 [`rcvr] 为接收器，并令 [`op_state] 为与 [`rcvr] 连接到某个发送器所
创建的异步操作相关联的操作状态。

[:en] Let [`token] be a stop token equal to [`get_stop_token(get_env(rcvr))].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`token] 为等于 [`get_stop_token(get_env(rcvr))] 的停止令牌。

[:en] [`token] shall remain valid for the duration of the
asynchronous operation[=']s lifetime ([#exec.async.ops]).
[:zh_CN] [`token] 在该异步操作的生存期（[#exec.async.ops]）持续期间应当一直有效。

[begin:note]
[:en] This means that, unless it knows about further guarantees
provided by the type of [`rcvr], the implementation of [`op_state] cannot use
[`token] after it executes a completion operation.
[:zh_CN] 这意味着，除非 [`op_state] 的实现已知 [`rcvr] 的类型提供的进一步保证，否则
它不能在执行完成操作之后使用 [`token]。

[:en] This also implies that any stop callbacks registered on [`token]
must be destroyed before the invocation of the completion operation.
[:zh_CN] 这也意味着，[`token] 上注册的任何停止回调，都必须在完成操作的调用之前销毁。
[end:note]

[para]
[codeblock:synopsis]
namespace std::execution {
  template<class Rcvr, class ChildOp>
    concept [[redoc("`:c@def>")]]inlinable_receiver = [[redoc("`:c>")]]receiver<Rcvr> &&
      requires (ChildOp* child) {
        { remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>::make_receiver_for(child) } noexcept
          -> [[redoc("`:c>")]]same_as<remove_cvref_t<Rcvr>>;
      };
}
[codeblock:end]

[:en] The [`:c inlinable_receiver] concept defines the requirements for a receiver
that can be reconstructed on demand from a pointer to the operation state object
created when the receiver was connected to a sender.
[:zh_CN] [`:c inlinable_receiver] 概念定义对接收器的要求，接收器可以根据连接到发送器时
创建的操作状态对象的指针按需重新构造。

[:en] Given a receiver object [`rcvr] of type [`Rcvr] which was connected to
a sender producing an operation state object [`op] of type [`Op],
[`Rcvr] models [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<Op>] only if the expression
[`Rcvr::make_receiver_for(addressof(op))] evaluates to a receiver
that is equal to [`rcvr] ([#concepts.equality]).
[:zh_CN] 给定 [`Rcvr] 类型的接收器对象 [`rcvr]，它已连接到某个发送器并产生类型为 [`Op] 的
操作状态对象 [`op]，只有当表达式 [`Rcvr::make_receiver_for(addressof(op))] 求值为
与 [`rcvr] 相等的接收器（[#concepts.equality]）时，[`Rcvr] 才构成 [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<Op>]。

[begin:note]
[:en] Such a receiver does not need to be stored as a data member of [`op]
as it can be recreated on demand.
[:zh_CN] 这样的接收器不需要作为 [`op] 的数据成员存储，因为它可以按需重新创建。
[end:note]

[:en] [`ChildOp] may be an incomplete type.
[:zh_CN] [`ChildOp] 可以是不完整类型。

[para]
[:en] Given objects [$O_0, \dotsc, O_n], [$O_n] is [+:adj transitively[!constructed]] from [$O_0] if
[:zh_CN] 给定对象 [$O_0, \dotsc, O_n]，如果满足以下条件，则 [$O_n] 是从 [$O_0] [+:adj 传递[!构造]]的：
[list]
[item]
[:en@~] [`remove_cvref_t<decltype([$O_n])>] denotes the same type as
[`remove_cvref_t<decltype([$O_0])>] and
[:zh_CN@~] [`remove_cvref_t<decltype([$O_n])>] 代表与 [`remove_cvref_t<decltype([$O_0])>] 相同的类型，并且
[item]
[:en@~] either
[:zh_CN@~] 要么
 [list]
 [item]
[:en@~] [$O_1] was initialized by decay-copying a reference to [$O_0], or
[:zh_CN@~] [$O_1] 是通过退化复制一个到 [$O_0] 的引用来初始化的，或者
 [item]
[:en@~] [$n > 1] and [$O_{n-1}] is transitively constructed from [$O_0] and
[$O_n] was initialized from a non-const, non-volatile rvalue reference to [$O_{n-1}].
[:zh_CN@~] [$n > 1] 并且 [$O_{n-1}] 是从 [$O_0] 传递构造的，并且 [$O_n] 是通过一个
非 const、非 volatile 的到 [$O_{n-1}] 的右值引用来初始化的。
 [list:end]
[list:end]

[para]
[:en] Let [$E] be some well-formed expression [`connect(sndr, rcvr)].
[:zh_CN] 令 [$E] 为某个良构表达式 [`connect(sndr, rcvr)]。

[:en] [$E] [+inlines the receiver] [`rcvr] if the lifetimes of all objects
transitively constructed from [`rcvr] during the evaluation of [$E]
end within the evaluation of [$E].
[:zh_CN] 如果在 [$E] 的求值过程中，从 [`rcvr] 传递构造的所有对象的生命周期
都在 [$E] 的求值过程中结束，则 [$E] [+内联接收器] [`rcvr]。

[begin:note]
[:en] This means such an expression does not store the receiver in the operation state.
[:zh_CN] 这意味着这样的表达式不在操作状态中存储接收器。
[end:note]

[para]
[:en] Let [$E] be some well-formed expression [`connect(sndr, rcvr)] where
[:zh_CN] 令 [$E] 为某个良构表达式 [`connect(sndr, rcvr)]，其中
[list]
[item]
[:en@~] [`sndr] denotes a sender type defined by this document and
[:zh_CN@~] [`sndr] 代表某个由本文档定义的发送器类型，而
[item]
[:en@~] [$E] inlines the receiver [`rcvr].
[:zh_CN@~] [$E] 内联接收器 [`rcvr]。
[list:end]

[:en] Then, let [`op] be the result of the evaluation of [$E], and
wherever the specification of the operation associated with [`op] contains a glvalue
which would denote an object transitively constructed from [`rcvr],
that glvalue instead denotes the result of applying
the temporary materialization conversion to the expression
[`remove_cvref_t<decltype(rcvr)>::make_receiver_for(addressof(op))].
[:zh_CN] 从而，令 [`op] 为 [$E] 的求值结果，并且在与 [`op] 相关联的操作的规范中，
包含任何表示从 [`rcvr] 传递构造的对象的泛左值，则该泛左值改为表示对表达式
[`remove_cvref_t<decltype(rcvr)>::make_receiver_for(addressof(op))]
实施临时对象实质化转换的结果。

[para]
[:en] Let [`StdRcvr] be a receiver type defined by this document.
[:zh_CN] 令 [`StdRcvr] 为本文档定义的某个接收器类型。

[:en] Given some operation state type [`Op], it is unspecified
whether [`StdRcvr] models [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<Op>].
[:zh_CN] 给定某个操作状态类型 [`Op]，未指明 [`StdRcvr] 是否构成 [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<Op>]。

[para]
[:en] Let [`StdOp] be some operation state type defined by this document,
and let [`Sndr] and [`Rcvr] be types such that
[`is_same_v<connect_result_t<Sndr, Rcvr>, StdOp>] is [`true].
[:zh_CN] 令 [`StdOp] 为本文档定义的某个操作状态类型，并且令 [`Sndr] 和 [`Rcvr] 是使得
[`is_same_v<connect_result_t<Sndr, Rcvr>, StdOp>] 为 [`true] 的类型。

[:en] If [`Rcvr] models [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<StdOp>]
then it is implementation-defined whether, given an object [`rcvr] of type [`Rcvr],
the [`connect] operation which produces an object of type [`StdOp]
inlines the receiver [`rcvr].
[:zh_CN] 如果 [`Rcvr] 构成 [`[`:c inlinable_receiver]<StdOp>]，给定某个 [`Rcvr] 类型的
对象 [`rcvr]，产生类型为 [`StdOp] 的对象的 [`connect] 操作是否内联接收器 [`rcvr] 是由实现定义的。
